					Jump to:					 navigation , 					 search Louisiana's  4th congressional district Louisiana's 4th congressional district - since January 3, 2013. Current Representative Mike Johnson   ( R – Benton ) Distribution 59.24% urban 40.76% rural Population (2000) 638,466 Median income 31,085 Ethnicity 73.0%  White 18.5%  Black 1.2%  Asian 5.0%  Hispanic 1.5%  Native American 0.8% other Cook PVI R+13 [1] Louisiana's 4th congressional district  is a  congressional district  in the  U.S. state  of  Louisiana . The district is located in the northwestern part of the state and is based in  Shreveport - Bossier City . It also includes the cities of  Minden ,  DeRidder , and  Natchitoches . The district is represented by  Republican   Mike Johnson . Contents 1   History 2   List of representatives 3   Recent election results 3.1   2002 3.2   2004 3.3   2006 3.4   2008 3.5   2010 4   Historical district boundaries 5   See also 6   References History 